Tak Laird of Glengarnock off the kirk of Balfrone.

45 Be It kend till all men be thir present lettres Me J ames Commendatar of Incheffray fforsamekill as Sr J ames Cuninghame of Glengarnock knicht and his predecessores Lairdis of Glengarnok hes bene kyndlie tenentis and takismen in tyme bygane past memorie of man . . . off all . . . the personage and vicarage teyndis of the Kirk of Balfrone quhilk is ane of the proper kirkis of the said abbacie . . . to haif sett . . . witht the aduyse and consent of Dene Alexander Murray ane of the conventis of the said abbacie now onlie on lyfe and witht the aduise and consent of Sr Duncane Camp- bell of Glenurquhy knicht at quhais instance I the said J ames Commendatar of Incheffray am interdytit for 1118 entres and sic lyke witht the aduise and consent of Sir J ohnne Drummond of Innerpeffrie knicht eldest sone and apperand air to me the said James . . . to the said ΒΓ James Cunynghame of Glengarnok knycht . . . the teind scheavis fruetis rentis prouentis emolimentis baith of the said personage and vicarage of the said kirk of Balfrone . . . for tuenty ane yeiris . . .
